CITI on Godrej Cons
Buy, TP Rs 1300
Management meet Key takeaways
(a) Demand trends remain fairly stable so far despite commodity cost inflation and a subsequent price hike to mitigate the impact.
(b) Mgmt. reiterated its expectations of achieving high-single-digit volume growth in FY27.
(c) Growth construct to be driven by the ‘Speedboats’ growing at 30%+ over the medium-term.
(d) New category creation through innovation could potentially create the future Speedboats segments.

CITI on Colgate
Sell, TP Rs 2050
Management meet Key takeaways
1) growth trajectory should be more balanced; a favorable base is helping;
2) pricing is returning, but net realization may remain moderated by competitive intensity;
3) premiumization remains key structural growth lever;
4) margin trade-offs are likely to persist despite healthy gross margins.

CITI on Trent
Sell, TP Rs 2733
Management meet Key takeaways
(a) demand appears to be holding up reasonably well;
(b) supply-side remain noisy across RM (polyester/cotton), labour availability, etc;
(c) inflation impact in the medium-term is limited as consumers continue to consume, but share shifts across players can be meaningful;
(d) prefer not to pass on the entire cost impact and instead solve through interventions across product, sourcing and operations;
(e) real estate remains an important variable, but Trent’s asymmetric lease structures continue to provide a strong option value;
(f) Zudio’s opportunity appears larger than earlier envisaged, with a higher share of India ready for the brand;
(g) Trent continues to evaluate lifestyle adjacencies — jewellery, accessories, beauty, fragrance and home — while Star is now in a better place and remains an interesting long-term opportunity.

CITI on Crompton Cons
Buy, TP Rs 400
Management meet Key takeaways
(a) demand has started to improve, helped by strong summer and partly led by low base;
(b) Crompton’s products are relatively non-discretionary, but sticker (price) shock can defer purchases and channel elasticity can shift share across brands;
(c) Crompton has taken 4 rounds of price hikes in fans aggregating ~9–10% (~12–13% vs 3Q levels) – however, other industry players have not taken the requisite price hike;
(d) structural initiatives over the last 3 years — GTM, cost reset, lighting turnaround, Butterfly recovery, SDA growth, solar pumps/rooftop, and wires — are starting to show results
(e) near-term priority is revenue growth, while margin recovery should be more visible through FY27.

